- &quot;The Physics of Glaciers&quot;, 4th edition (c2010), by Kurt M. Cuffey &amp; W. S. B. Paterson.
INFO: &lt;a href=&quot; http://store.elsevier.com/product.jsp?isbn=9780123694614&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt; http://store.elsevier.com/product.jsp?isbn=9780123694614&lt;/a&gt;

- &quot;Fundamentals of Glacier Dynamics&quot;, 2nd edition (c2013), by C. J. van der Veen.
INFO: &lt;a href=&quot; http://www.crcpress.com/product/isbn/9781439835661&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt; http://www.crcpress.com/product/isbn/9781439835661&lt;/a&gt;

(foldered in &quot;Physics of Glaciers, Glacier Mechanics, Glacier Dynamics 3-pack&quot;)


AUDIENCE: Grad students, academic and pro researchers in the fields of glaciology, climatology, geophysics and geology.

WARNING: These books were repaired from a slightly broken state. The repairs made though are not fully compliant with the PDF standard and for this reason files won't display correctly (graphs and figures missing here and there) in standard abiding Adobe softwares. Tested OK using Foxit Reader and PDF-XChange Viewer.
